tepegoz-ids (0.2.3) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Refine Volumetric Flood alerts to prevent micro-flow rate-spike false positives:
    - Split generic Volumetric Flood rule into PPS, Bps, and Cross-Flow rules.
    - Set logic to 'all' to enforce minimum packet count, byte count, and flow count thresholds.

 -- Tepegoz IDS Team <maintainers@tepegoz.local>  Wed, 20 May 2026 00:30:00 +0300

tepegoz-ids (0.2.2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Eliminate return-traffic false positives in Port Scan detection:
    - Restrict syn_count increments to pure SYN packets (excluding SYN-ACK).
    - Track flow protocol in SourceTracker.
    - Ignore TCP return flows (syn_count == 0) when computing unique destination ports.
    - Add EXCLUDE_PORTS configuration support in sensor.conf, defaulting to 32768-60999.

 -- Tepegoz IDS Team <maintainers@tepegoz.local>  Wed, 20 May 2026 00:10:00 +0300

tepegoz-ids (0.2.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix alert database-to-UI pipeline:
    - Pass evaluated direction parameter to AlertRecord.
    - Inject default values for direction, severity, and rule_name tags in Flux query.
    - Prevent query failures due to database schema changes or empty fields.

 -- Tepegoz IDS Team <maintainers@tepegoz.local>  Tue, 19 May 2026 22:20:00 +0300

tepegoz-ids (0.2.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Schema-driven rule engine: rules defined entirely in YAML (field/op/value).
  * Cross-flow correlation: detects port scans and SYN floods across micro-flows.
  * Alert cooldown: suppresses duplicate alerts per rule+source for 30 seconds.
  * Dashboard: rule name dropdown filter, column reorder, severity color-coding.
  * 5 new detection rules: UDP Flood, DNS Amplification, C2 Beacon,
    Data Exfiltration, Suspicious Long Flow.
  * Direction passed to rule engine for directional detection.

 -- Tepegoz IDS Team <maintainers@tepegoz.local>  Mon, 19 May 2026 20:10:00 +0000

